comment:
* Provides the barring configuration for a particular service type.
 *
 * Provides indication about the barring of a particular service for use. Certain barring types
 * are only valid for certain technology families. Any service that does not have a barring
 * configuration is unbarred by default.

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_CS_SERVICE
variables.comment: Barring indicator for circuit-switched service; applicable to UTRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_PS_SERVICE
variables.comment: Barring indicator for packet-switched service; applicable to UTRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_CS_VOICE
variables.comment: Barring indicator for circuit-switched voice service; applicable to UTRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_MO_SIGNALLING
variables.comment: Barring indicator for mobile-originated signalling; applicable to EUTRAN and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_MO_DATA
variables.comment: Barring indicator for mobile-originated data traffic; applicable to EUTRAN and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_CS_FALLBACK
variables.comment: Barring indicator for circuit-switched fallback for voice; applicable to EUTRAN and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_MMTEL_VOICE
variables.comment: Barring indicator for MMTEL (IMS) voice; applicable to EUTRAN and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_MMTEL_VIDEO
variables.comment: Barring indicator for MMTEL (IMS) video; applicable to EUTRAN and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_EMERGENCY
variables.comment: Barring indicator for emergency services; applicable to UTRAN, EUTRAN, and NGRAN

variables.name: BARRING_SERVICE_TYPE_SMS
variables.comment: Barring indicator for SMS sending; applicable to UTRAN, EUTRAN, and NGRAN

variables.name: mBarringServiceInfos
variables.comment: that describes the current barring status of that particular service.
